comments: 2212788 square kilometers. The Blossom River is a clearwater river (not glacially influenced). The  chinook salmon stock is a "spring" stock.  Mature fish migrate through terminal marine waters in Southeast Alaska in May through early July.  These fish enter the lower  River in June and July. Chinook salmon are counted 2-4 times per season by foot in the two largest tributaries to the Unuk River (Cripple and Genes Lake creeks) and by helicopter in an additional four tributaries.  The highest single-day count, summed across all index areas in the river, is used as the escapement index for that year

source: McPherson, S.A. and J.H. Clark.  In Prep.  Biological escapement goal for King Salmon River chinook salmon.   Alaska Department of Fish and Game, Division of Sport Fish, Fishery Manuscript Report, Anchorage. (907-465-4270).
comments: 1327672 sq. meters rearing habitat. The King Salmon River is a relatively small clearwater system on Admiralty Island in Southeast Alaska that drains an area of about 100 km2 . The King Salmon River chinook salmon stock is a "spring" stock.  Mature fish migrate through terminal marine waters in Southeast Alaska in May and June.  Maturing adults enter the river primarily in July. Chinook salmon were counted through a weir located near tidewater from 1983-1992 and counted all large chinook (3 to 5-ocean-age) and jacks (2-ocean age-no 1-ocean-age jacks have been observed for this stock, but may be present in some years).
